    "Interestingly, most of these methods were developed for pre-training on molecule-in-vacuum systems, thus limiting the downstream tasks to such a class of tasks.",
    "Gardner et al.",
    "76 developed pre-trained models for condensedphase carbon systems, but these models are unlikely to be generalizable to systems composed of chemical elements other than carbon.",
    "Zhang et al.",
    "43 pre-trained the DPA-1 model on the OC2M dataset 77 and examined its performance on downstream tasks involving high entropy alloys and AlMgCu ternary alloys."
